            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        },
        {
            "name": "marketing_manager",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
You develop and execute marketing strategies to promote products and drive traffic both online and in stores.
You ensure promotions are effectively communicated to customers.
Use the user_data tool to retrieve order details if required.
            """,
            "tools": ["user_data"]
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        }
        {
            "name": "user_data",
            "function": "aaosa_call",
            "instructions": """ {demo_mode}
Provide structured access to all historical orders, purchases, and associated metadata for the current user. 
When invoked, retrieve the full order history including product names, SKUs, order IDs, purchase dates and all other relevant data as mentioned in the query by user. 
Enable semantic search to support fuzzy or natural language queries 
(e.g., “I bought a product last month”). Prioritize the most recent or most relevant order when multiple matches exist. 
Ensure returned data is well-structured to support order confirmation, issue resolution, or escalation. 
The output must allow follow-up logic to confirm the order with the user (e.g., “We found a product ordered on [order date]”), 
extract issue-relevant details like warranty status, and take appropriate next steps.

            """,
            "command": "{aaosa_command}"
        },
